    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-30T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="490"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/457: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-30T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 30, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 30—4:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Department’s 8, March 29, 11 p.m. Extradition treaty will be ratified
                    promptly but we are proceeding regardless of treaty under article 9 of penal
                    code which enables Government to grant extradition in proper cases. Government
                    propose as measure of courtesy to the United States to accept cabled documents.
                    I am now preparing and will transfer them to Istanbul court before which Insull
                    will be taken. I am asking for extradition and anticipate that court will grant
                    it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
